  "prompt": "What did cavemen eat?",
  "response": "Cavemen, or prehistoric humans during the Paleolithic era, had a varied diet that depended on their location, climate, and available resources. Their diet typically included:\n\n1. Meat from hunting:\n- Large game animals\n- Small mammals\n- Birds\n- Fish\n\n2. Gathered plant foods:\n- Berries\n- Fruits\n- Nuts\n- Seeds\n- Roots\n- Leafy greens\n- Mushrooms\n\n3. Foraged foods:\n- Wild honey\n- Eggs\n- Insects\n\n4. Later developments:\n- Cooked foods (after discovering fire)\n- Grains (towards the end of the Paleolithic period)\n\nTheir diet was generally high in protein, varied in nutrients, and mostly unprocessed. The availability of food depended on seasonal changes and migration patterns. Hunting and gathering required significant physical effort and skill, and the diet was more diverse and nutrient-dense compared to modern processed diets.\n\nThe specific composition of their diet varied by region, with some groups having more meat-based diets (like in colder regions) and others having more plant-based diets (in areas with abundant vegetation).",
